frugal /ˈfruːɡəl/

1. ADJ People who are frugal or who live frugal lives do not spend much money on themselves. 俭朴的 

例： She lives a frugal life. 她过着俭朴的生活。 

2. frugality N-UNCOUNT 俭朴 

例： We must practise the strictest frugality and economy. 我们必须奉行最严格意义上的俭朴和节约。 

3. ADJ A frugal meal is small and not expensive. (膳食) 俭省的 

例： The diet was frugal: cheese and water, rice and beans. 饮食很俭省：奶酪和水，米饭和豆类。

